OL,3,CMark Robins appointed manager of Stoke
OL,4,CCity
OL,6,FMark Robins has been appointed manager
OL,7,Fof Stoke City on a three-and-a-half-
OL,8,Fyear contract.
OL,10,FThe 55-year-old will be in the dugout
OL,11,Ffor the first time against Plymouth
OL,12,FArgyle at the bet365 Stadium on
OL,13,FSaturday, with Ryan Shawcross
OL,14,Fcontinuing as caretaker at Burnley
OL,15,Ftoday.
OL,17,FReporting to Sporting Director Jon
OL,18,FWalters, the new appointment arrives
OL,19,Fin ST4 after overseeing a dynasty of
OL,20,Fsuccess over seven years with Coventry
OL,21,FCity.
